@cooked2
on-arrival: dnvp_party_leader = "Kuno von Westarp"; dnvp_ideology = "National Conservatism"; old_middle_dnvp += 5; rural_dnvp += 3; workers_dnvp -= 3; new_middle_dnvp -= 5; pro_republic -= 5; nationalism += 5; dnvp_relation -= 20

= Lambach falls on the second vote!

With Hugenberg's bloc already gone, it was the quiet defection of the Moderates and the resolute Traditionalists that finished him. The Christian Socials fought to the last, but without the broader coalition Lambach once relied upon, the numbers were simply not there.

Walther Lambach steps down from the chairmanship, his experiment in remaking the DNVP ending in defeat.

[Your consequences here]

@survives2
on-arrival: lambach_stage = 2; workers_dnvp += 5; new_middle_dnvp += 5

= Lambach survives a second time — his grip is iron!

Against all expectations, Walther Lambach has beaten back a second attempt to remove him. The rump opposition, stripped of Hugenberg's resources and organisation, could not muster enough votes even among the Traditionalists and Moderates to cross the threshold.

His position is now unassailable. The dissenters have exhausted every parliamentary tool available to them. What remains of the old DNVP either falls in line — or leaves.

[Your consequences here]
